 :social engineering: n. Term used among {cracker}s and {samurai} for
cracking techniques that rely on weaknesses in {wetware} rather than
software; the aim is to trick people into revealing passwords or other
information that compromises a target system's security. Classic scams
include phoning up a mark who has the required information and posing as a
field service tech or a fellow employee with an urgent access problem. see
also the {tiger team} story in the {patch} entry, and {rubber-hose
cryptanalysis}.